Female: Same as the male except cephalothorax lighter brown and without dorsal stripes. Epigynum (
Figs 75–76
): sclerotised, with two O-shaped lateral fossae and with distinctive, well separated copulatory openings. Insemination ducts of short/medium length passing anterior to the fossae, spermathecae rounded, larger than the fossae. Dimensions: CL 2.18 ± 0.09 ( 11 ), EFL 0.88 ± 0.03 ( 11 ), CW 1.55 ± 0.06 ( 11 ), AEW 1.40 ± 0.07 ( 11 ), AMEW 0.88 ± 0.05 ( 11 ), PEW 1.39 ± 0.06 ( 11 ), SL 0.97 ± 0.03 , ( P 4 + T 4 ) 1.57 ± 0.02 ( 11 ).

Distribution: Known from scattered localities in both the coastal and Andean forests (
Fig. 79
).
